 help people around the world through corporate giving and employeevolunteer programs that span across six pillars education health care social services arts and culture sports and environment in  the bank contributed  million in donations and sponsorships to community causes around the world scotiabanks employees spent  hours in  volunteering and fundraising through formal community programs scotiabanks corporate social responsibility ecoliving program encourages and facilitates environmentally preferable construction and renovation of homes the company also has internal programs related to environmental responsibility and ethical financial and lending practices recent eventsedit on october   scotiabank acquired a  stake in colpatria es colombias fifth largest bank and second largest issuer of credit cards for the tune of  billion canadian dollars in cash and stock  million shares it is the second largest foreign transaction ever by a canadian financial company overseas behind royal bank of canadas purchase in royal bank of trinidad and tobago on august   scotiabank announced that it would acquire ing direct canada for  billion the sale was completed on november   on july   scotiabank announced that it would buy citigroups retail and commercial banking operations in panama and costa rica terms of the transaction were not disclosed the purchase would increase scotiabanks client base in both countries from  to  and would add  branches to the existing  branches in both central american nations scotiabank has a strong presence in thailand through its  owned affiliate thanachart bank with the recent acquisition of siam city bank thanachart bank is now the th largest bank by assets in thailand with over  staff serving more than four million customers through  branches and  atms across the country scotiabanks former president ceo and chairman cedric ritchie died on march   he was a president of scotiabank from  and ceo and chairman from  to  he was made an officer of the 